        <a name="whatsNew"></a>
        <h3>What's new</h3>
        <p>The latest release includes the following enhancements:</p>
        <ul>
			<li>Mapping
				<ul>
					<li>You can now browse and select the 2015 Dominant Tapestry Segment when creating a Color-Coded Map in the US. </li>
					<li>Access to Web Maps is now also available from the "Create Maps From Data" menu. </li>
					<li>New  options in Preferences are available to change color and thickness of boundary borders.</li>
					<li>The ability to display boundary borders and labels is now available for all countries</li>
				</ul></li>
			<li>Display Enhancements for Sites, Businesses, and Imported Points
				<ul>
					<li>Import and store your own logo and use it to represent locations that you import or business locations from Business and Facilities Search.</li>
					<li>Set the default symbol for Sites, Imported Files, and Business Search results.</li>
					<li>New options for displaying point data are now available and controlled by a new mapping option in Import File and in Business and Facilities Search.</li>
					<li>Reorder saved variables.</li>
				</ul></li>
			<li>New ways to create trade areas
				<ul>
					<li>Create trade areas around sites based on <a href="/en/bao/help/essential-vocabulary.htm#ESRI_SECTION1_32513CD49FF5424889AA777188027A94">walk time</a> or distance.  Walk times follow paths and roads that allow pedestrian traffic and find solutions that optimize travel time/distance.</li>
					<li>Reports using Bands (or Donuts) can be applied to rings, <a href="/en/bao/help/essential-vocabulary.htm#ESRI_SECTION1_65FC7F19BC634F3085D37AC238659103">drive times</a>, and walk times.</li>
					<li>More options are available for Drive Time analysis including travel mode (driving, rural driving, and trucking), direction to or from facility, and traffic. Traffic options include live traffic or traffic based on typical conditions.</li>
				</ul></li>
			<li>Content Updates
				<ul>
					<li>Infogroup is the new Business Locations/Business Search provider in the U.S. and Canada.</li>
					<li>Retail MarketPlace Profile and data have been updated to include business summary counts from Infogroup.</li>
					<li>Major Shopping Center Locator and <a href="/en/bao/help/essential-vocabulary.htm#ESRI_SECTION1_5D57C42EFBC34D00A45404A7D8DDC220">Major Shopping Center</a> Map have been updated to include June 2015 data from Directory of Major Malls (DMM).</li>
					<li>Advanced Demographic Datasets are now available.</li>
					<li>Users can choose either the Standard data from Michael Bauer Research (MBR) or the Advanced data.</li>
					<li>Canada 2015 demographic updates (from Environics Analytics)</li>
					<li>Updates to 45 other countries (Standard MBR Data Update).</li>
				</ul></li>
		</ul>


        <a name="systemRequirements"></a>
        <h3>System requirements</h3>

		<ul>
		 <li>Business Analyst requires an account that is part of an ArcGIS Online organization and is a member of a group with access to the Business Analyst Application.</li>
		 <li>Business Analyst supports the following browsers: Internet Explorer 9+<b>*</b>, Chrome (latest), Firefox (latest), and Safari (latest for Windows<b>*</b> and Mac OS X).<br>
		 <b>*</b> Some features will not work in Internet Explorer 9 and Safari for Windows.</li>
		</ul>
		
